ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Set up in 1984 the activities of Academy Theatre centre round one primary objective: to make a research into the history of the stage, particularly its music, in a term Natyasangeet, along with allied performing arts and try to revive the interest of the masses in this fond remembrance through productions, publications and preservations. With the objective, Academy Theatre has regularly manifested the research based concepts pertaining to the stage and its songs. Nearly 40 productions have been performed with high reputation and appreciation till date. Seminars, workshops and exhibitions on music, theatre, jatra, puppetry and paintings are being held regularly. Academy Theatre has presented educative as well as entertaining programmes on the several regional channels and also on the national network of Doordarshan. Academy Theatre has participated with its varied presentations in the national and international festivals in and outside the country. Moreover, Academy Theatre has published a biographical compilation in Bengali on Vincent Van Gogh and with its archival preservations, has enriched a number of definitive publications in the field of performing arts and literature. To be specific, the archival preservations of Academy Theatre include a wide range of materials: manuscripts date back to 1779, slide and photographs date back to 1869 , musical instruments date back to 18th century , and audio-video discs as also cassettes of live recordings of the performing personalities and events related to stage and music, not only of Bengal, but also of, all over India and abroad. While published materials date back to 1816, the library has over 8000 books and issues of over 800 periodicals in its stock. A large number of holdings are novel, rare and hardly available anywhere else. These things apart, the respective performers of theatrical and musical companies of yore are provided with financial and other required assistance, to the best of its ability, by Academy Theatre.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: AGNISH, a theatre group, was found on 13th November 2005 with a dream to breathe in a beautiful society, a well decorated environment where people from all cast and creed live happily, cheerfully and peacefully. Some young theatre lovers who want to say something about themselves, about their society through theatre are the members of Agnish. Agnish wants to befriend everyone with theatre. PRODUCTION OF PLAYS: Agnish has produced 6 full length plays and 7 short plays which have received wide appreciation from the press and the audience. To celebrate the bicentennial birth anniversary of Derozio, Agnish has produced the play JHAR written by Utpal Dutta. PERFORMANCES: Agnish regularly performs their shows in different places of West Bengal and nearby states. Agnish participated in the festivals organized by Department of Culture, West Bengal. Agnish has also performed their show on invitation from Easter Zonal Cultural Centre. THEATRE IN EDUCATION: To provide scientific education on theatre to the children Agnish has established AGNISH NATYA NIKETAN. We have got a number of 50 children who are keenly interested to take this opportunity. Agnish conducts regular theatre workshops for youth to concentrate them in different theatre activities. SEMINAR: Agnish regularly organizes seminars as a part of its research project on the important cultural events to educate and enlighten the theatre workers and theatre lovers. FESTIVALS: During the last 2 years, Agnish organizes theatre festivals AGNISH NATYA SAMMELAN to coordinate and establish common bonding with the groups and obviously with the theatre lovers of our locality. AWARDS: For excellence in production, Agnish has received many awards in full length plays competitions and in short play competitions as best production, best director and best actors. ACHIEVEMENTS: Beside overwhelming support from the audiences, Agnish has received grants from MoC, Govt. of India which have helped us in a great way to flourish more.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Our endeavor started in 1979, with one small rented room with one autistic child and one special educator. Now after 35 years of hard work we have grown to have a full-fledged special school for challenged children. We have been running a special schooland a Vocational training Unit for Autistic and mentally challenged children. Students from economically disadvantaged families receive education and training free of any charges, while others pay a substantially reduced rate. We aim to enable as many of our students as possible to get back to main stream schools and find an independent livelihood. Our team comprises special educators, co-curricular teachers in dance, music, rhythm, art & crafts, sports etc., and specialists namely physiotherapist, occupational therapist, speech therapists and psychologist and caregivers. There are two special school buses with wheelchair-hoist donated by Rotary Club of Calcutta Metropolitan and Life Insurance Corporation of India. We have an arrangement with Singapore International Foundation who depute expert teachers from their reputed special schools to conduct training workshop for our teachers and parents in Kolkata.
